40|$|Differential Medicare {{payments}} for hospital-based and freestanding skilled nursing facilities (SNFs) were eliminated by the SNF prospective payment system initiated in 1998. Closures and high negative margins of hospital-based facilities have prompted {{consideration of the}} need to revisit <b>payment</b> <b>adjustments</b> for this group of SNFs. We examine case mix-related and other factors behind the cost differences between hospital-based and freestanding SNFs. Some <b>payment</b> <b>adjustment,</b> notably for nontherapy ancillary services, may be reasonable for the short term. The differential Medicare {{payments for}} hospital-based and freestanding skilled nursing facilities (SNFs) have long been a controversial public pol-icy issue. At the heart of the issue are the reported higher costs of hospital-based SNFs relative to those of freestanding SNFs. Controversy has ex-isted over whether Medicare should recognize the causes behind the cost differences as appro...|$|R
